Class ModelIntegrityException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ModelIntegrityException
extends ModelException
    ModelIntegrityException is an exception class used for errors that arise due to issues with the integrity of the data model. For example, if the entry representing a defined supervisor cannot be found.
    See Also:
